> <OLD>
>
> There was a nod from WHEELIE, and he went over into the room.  At this
> ponit, as he went in to chat with Rodimus, he instinctively checked about
> the room for booby traps, signs fo security or other such things around.

<NEW>

The room was much like it was when WHEELIE saw it last. The room was
dominated by the medical bed upon which RODIMUS PRIME lay. The rest of
the room was fairly standard for a private repair chamber. A small
closet was off to one side, shelves, a small table a computer
interface console, presumably for the doctors and staff, but could be
set to allow the patient limit access as well.

The only door apparently leading out of the room was the one that
WHEELIE was using, and there were no windows, the only light coming
from overhead lamps.

RODIMUS looked up as WHEELIE opened the door, he much better than he
did last time, his optics bright and clear. "Wheelie!" He said a smile
on his face as he sat up. "Tell me, what's going on?" RODIMUS gestured
at the room at large, "These nurses and doctors won't tell me
anything."

(TAG)

Preston
